[
{ type: install
  message: <<EOM
PondSec NDR has been installed.

Recommended first checks:
  service configd restart
  configctl pondsecndr diagnostics
  configctl pondsecndr model_selftest

Suricata EVE JSON is the recommended telemetry source. Optional TLS inspection
through an already configured local Zenarmor or Squid deployment can improve
HTTP/TLS visibility, but PondSec NDR does not enable TLS interception by itself.

The default mode is monitor/learning. AI and baseline anomaly alarms should stay
in learning mode for the configured baseline period unless an administrator
accepts the false-positive risk of early activation.
EOM
}
{ type: remove
  message: <<EOM
PondSec NDR package files were removed.

The deinstall script can keep or remove configuration, database telemetry,
model artifacts, and PondSec-created PF table entries. For unattended cleanup,
set PONDSEC_KEEP_CONFIG, PONDSEC_KEEP_DATABASE, PONDSEC_KEEP_MODELS, and
PONDSEC_REMOVE_PF_BLOCKS before running pkg delete.
EOM
}
]
